## Summary: Phase 31 - Spell Checking System Migration

The plan at `/home/overlord/.claude/plans/scalable-snuggling-pebble.md` described migrating the spell checking system to Rust. Upon executing the plan, I discovered that **the spell crate is already substantially complete**:

### Current State

The `spell` crate (`src/nvim-rs/spell/`) contains:

| Module | Lines | Description |
|--------|-------|-------------|
| `lib.rs` | 3,752 | Core types, opaque handles, FFI bindings, file format constants |
| `spellfile.rs` | 3,279 | Binary .spl file reading/writing utilities |
| `suggest.rs` | 2,061 | Edit distance algorithms, suggestion scoring |
| `wordtree.rs` | 907 | Word tree traversal, binary search |
| `check.rs` | 803 | Spell checking utilities, case folding |
| **Total** | **10,802** | - |

The crate exports **144 FFI functions** callable from C, covering:
- Word tree traversal (`rs_tree_count_words`, `rs_traverse_tree`, `rs_tree_binary_search`)
- Edit distance scoring (`rs_spell_edit_score`, `rs_spell_edit_score_limit`)
- File I/O helpers (`rs_parse_*`, `rs_write_*` for all .spl section types)
- Suggestion scoring (`rs_score_*`, `rs_rescore`, `rs_maxscore`)
- Byte manipulation for suggestions (`rs_swap_bytes`, `rs_delete_byte`, `rs_insert_byte`)

